bullet: '''Optional:''' change if the preferred list separator is different from · (•) in your language. Do not change otherwise. For example, it is — in Russian. Do not use HTML entities, those are just provided for example.
separator: '''Optional:''' change if the preferred separator (for example, "!meow – help") is different from – (–) in your language. Do not change otherwise. For example, it is — (—) in Russian, Belarusian and Ukrainian. Keep the space at the start unless your language does not use them for separation. Do not use HTML entities, those are just provided for example.
comma: '''Optional:''' change if the preferred comma styling is different from , with a space in your language. Do not change otherwise. [https://translatewiki.net/w/i.php?title=Special:Translations&message=MediaWiki%3AComma-separator MediaWiki:Comma-separator] is the similar message in MediaWiki locale. Use it as a guidance.
yes:
Used to indicate that true/false value is true.
{{Identical|Yes}}
no:
Used to indicate that true/false value is false.
{{Identical|No}}
help-title: The header of !help command without parameters. {{Identical|Help}}
help-title-command: Title of the !help command in the bot. * {0} – command name (help). * {1} – command prefix (!). Leave {msg:separator} untranslated.
help-version: Version of the bot, displayed in !help command. {0} is the version. Example: 2.4.0. {{Identical|Version}}
help-repo: Link to [[w:Source code|source code]] of the bot. {0} is the link text.
help-default: The default value of a parameter. {0} is the default value. The message to translate is formatted using the Markdown syntax.
configuring-status: Used in a jokey bot response to inform whether the bot is functional. "Socket" here is [[:w:AC power plugs and sockets|an AC power socket]]. :information_source: should not be translated. The message is formatted using the Markdown syntax.
configuring-status-streaming: Used in the bot response to inform about whether the recent changes streams are functional. * {0} – number of minutes since the latest response. * {1} – number of seconds since the latest response. The message to translate is formatted using the Markdown syntax.
configuring-changed-answerBots: The bot response to setting !serverAnswerBots command. {0} here is not plural, it is true/false value. Translatewiki may force you to write the message according to plural rules. Only first two values will be used.
configuring-changed-domain: The bot response to a successful change in domain configuration for recent changes streams. {0} is a domain. Example: ru.wikipedia.org. The message to translate is formatted using the Markdown syntax.
configuring-changed-lang: The bot response to changing the language of the bot on a server. {0} is a language code and an autonym of the language. Example: ru (русский). The message to translate is formatted using the Markdown syntax.
configuring-changed-translatewiki: The bot response to enabling reports about recent changes on Translatewiki for a language. * {0} is a channel name. * {1} is a language code and an autonym of the language for which the reports were enabled. Example: ru (русский). The message to translate is formatted using the Markdown syntax.
configuring-changed-translatewiki-channe: The bot response to !guildTW command. {0} is the channel name.
configuring-changed-translatewiki-lang: The bot response to successful change in the language for which reports about Translatewiki changes are done. {0} is a language code and an autonym of the language. Example: ru (русский). The message to translate is formatted using the Markdown syntax.
configuring-changed-wiki: The bot response to successful change in wiki linking configuration. {0} is a wiki URL. The message to translate is formatted using the Markdown syntax.
configuring-changed-wiki-channel: The bot response to successful change in wiki linking configuration for a specific channel. {0} is a wiki URL. The message to translate is formatted using the Markdown syntax.
configuring-required-value: The error response when a user did not provide the value for a parameter. {1}help {0} should not be translated.
configuring-badvalue-domain: The error response in a case where a person tries to enable recent changes streams for non-Wikimedia wikis. {0} is a comma-separated list of Wikimedia projects’ domain names.
configuring-badvalue-wiki: The error response to an invalid URL for wiki linking configuration. {0} is a URL pattern that must be present in the URL. Example: /wiki/$1. The message to translate is formatted using the Markdown syntax.
configuring-help-wiki: The description of !guildWiki command. See also: {{msg-wm|Discordwikibot-configuring-help-wiki-channel}}
configuring-help-wiki-channel: The description of !channelWiki command. See also: {{msg-wm|Discordwikibot-configuring-help-wiki}}
linking-toolong: The error response in a case where the bot’s message with links gets longer than 2,000 characters, which is not allowed in Discord.
streaming-domain: Used in bot responses for other stream-related commands. * {0} is the current domain used by streams, for example, ru.wikipedia.org.
streaming-stream-namespace: Used in messages such as {{msg-wm|Discordwikibot-streaming-opened}}. {0} is a namespace number.
streaming-stream-title: Used in messages such as {{msg-wm|Discordwikibot-streaming-opened}}. {0} is a page title.
streaming-opened: The bot response when a new recent changes stream gets added into a channel. * {0} – stream target. Uses {{msg-wm|Discordwikibot-streaming-stream-title}} and {{msg-wm|Discordwikibot-streaming-stream-namespace}}. * {1} – channel name. * {2} – stream parameters. :white_check_mark: should not be translated.
streaming-edited: The bot response when parameters of a recent changes stream get changed in a channel. * {0} is a stream target. Uses {{msg-wm|Discordwikibot-streaming-stream-title}} and {{msg-wm|Discordwikibot-streaming-stream-namespace}}. * {1} is a channel name. * {2} are stream parameters in a list. :eight_spoked_asterisk: should not be translated.
streaming-edited-nothing: The bot response when a command changing parameters of a recent changes stream gets performed, but no changes happen. * {0} – stream target. Uses {{msg-wm|Discordwikibot-streaming-stream-title}} and {{msg-wm|Discordwikibot-streaming-stream-namespace}}. * {1} – channel name. :ok: should not be translated.
streaming-closed: The bot response when a recent changes stream gets removed from a channel. * {0} – stream target. Uses {{msg-wm|Discordwikibot-streaming-stream-title}} and {{msg-wm|Discordwikibot-streaming-stream-namespace}}. * {1} – channel name. :negative_squared_cross_mark: should not be translated.
streaming-list: The bot response about active recent changes streams on a server. * {0} is a number of active streams. * {1} is a list of streams. * {2} is {{msg-wm|Discordwikibot-domain}} message with the current domain. :information_source: should not be translated.
streaming-list-nothing: The bot response to !listStreams command when there are no active streams on a server. :ok: should not be translated.
streaming-list-stream: The subheader in a message informing about the number of active streams on a server. * {0} – stream target. Uses {{msg-wm|Discordwikibot-streaming-stream-title}} and {{msg-wm|Discordwikibot-streaming-stream-namespace}}. * {1} – number of active streams.
streaming-key-bot: Explanation for bot key of recent changes streams configuration. "Include" is a verb in infinitive form here.
streaming-key-in-comment: Explanation for in-comment key of recent changes streams configuration. "Search" is a verb in infinitive form here.
streaming-key-minor: Explanation for minor key of recent changes streams configuration. "Include" is a verb in infinitive form here.
streaming-key-patrolled: Explanation for patrolled key of recent changes streams. "Patrolling" is [[mw:Help:Patrolling|MediaWiki patrolling]] here. "Filter" is a verb in infinitive form here.
streaming-key-title: Explanation for title key of recent changes streams configuration. {{Identical|Page title}}
streaming-required-goal: The error response when a user did not provide the stream goal. {1}help {0} should not be translated. The message to translate is formatted using the Markdown syntax.
streaming-help-args: Please translate the first line only.
translatewiki-header: The header in a bot response about new messages on Translatewiki.net. * {0} – formatted number of messages. * {1} – unformatted number of messages. * {2} – number of authors that have edited those messages.
